fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.locale

Interface IDictionary

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAttachable

    @PluginService
public interface IDictionary
extends IAttachable
    Defines localized text strings or formattable templates.

    Implementations returned by ILocaleService.getDictionary(String, DictionaryType, FormatType) are automatically registered as plug-in OSGi services.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    ILocaleService.getDictionary(String, DictionaryType, FormatType), ILocaleService.getText(java.util.Locale, IDictionary, String, Object...)

    • Method Detail

      • getDictionaryName

        String getDictionaryName()
        Gets the name of the dictionary, which should be unique per bundle.

        For instances provided by the default implementation of ILocaleService, this will match the dictionaryName parameter.

        Returns:
        the non-null (and non-empty) dictionary name.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getDictionaryKeys

        Set<String> getDictionaryKeys()
        Gets the set of all keys in this dictionary.
        Returns:
        the set of dictionary keys.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getFormatType

        FormatType getFormatType()
        Gets the format type for any text templates stored by this dictionary. The format type determines how any templates are to be parsed when merging in dynamic information to produce localized text.

        For instances provided by the default implementation of ILocaleService, this will match the formatType parameter.

        Returns:
        the format type, or null if this dictionary is not expected to contain any text templates.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getTextLocales

        Set<Locale> getTextLocales(String key)
        Gets the available locales for the specified translation key.
        Parameters:
        key - the non-null translation key.
        Returns:
        the set of available locales, or an empty set (not null) if there are no translations for the specified key.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        ILocaleService.negotiateLocale(java.util.Locale, java.util.Collection), getLocalText(java.util.Locale, String)

      • getTextLocales

        Set<Locale> getTextLocales()
        Gets the complete set of locales used by this dictionary.

        Note: this does not imply that all keys have text in all locales. Use getTextLocales(key) to check.

        Returns:
        the set of available locales, or an empty set (not null) if this is an empty dictionary.
        Since:
        1.0
